HEADWORD: Journeywork
<hw>Jour"ney*work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Originally, work done by the day; work done by a journeyman at his
trade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Routine or relatively
unskilled work performed under direction of a supervisor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Joust</ent>⟦br⟧
